title: Background runners cannot use tmux as a persistent session host
---
ClawQ cannot currently host external Codex or Claude runners in named detached tmux sessions. A tmux backend is needed as a widely available fallback when Herdr is not installed and as a simple inspectable host for autonomous work items.\n\nAdd a tmux adapter to the session-host interface from B768. It must create collision-safe named sessions, launch the runner in the task worktree, capture output, deliver literal follow-up input safely, check liveness, terminate the session, expose the attach command, and recover or classify sessions after daemon restart. Prompt and issue text must not be shell-interpolated; use a safe argv/script-file or tmux buffer mechanism.\n\nAcceptance:\n- A background task can select host=tmux independently of runner=auto/codex/claude.\n- list/show/logs/message/wait/cancel map consistently onto the shared host lifecycle.\n- Session names are deterministic enough for recovery but collision-safe across ClawQ homes and task IDs.\n- Missing tmux, missing sessions, already-completed sessions, and failed startup have explicit negative tests.\n- Integration tests skip cleanly when tmux is unavailable.\n- Existing direct-process behavior remains the default until configuration explicitly selects or prefers tmux.